The two parties have diverged so greatly over the past few decades we no longer have overlapping views and any space for compromise. Instead we make decisions in the interest of our party and no longer think about what's best for our actual country and our people. Unless we can knock some sense into people, we are digger ourselves a deeper and deeper hole the longer we keep the two party system which is tearing our country apart. Some of the most intelligent and capable leaders in our country sit in the middle of our political spectrum. That's the type of leader I believe we need. One who can compromise, listen, and make progress. One who doesn't have an underlying agenda to turn our people against each other and divide us into rigid categories. Our system encourages people to choose the left or right, ultimately making the moderate voter/poltician powerless
